The '''blob''' is a [[monster class]] that appears in ''[[NetHack]]'', and is represented by the lowercase [[b]] glyph ({{white|b}}). Blobs are designated internally by the macro '''S_BLOB'''.{{refsrc|include/monsym.h|16|version=NetHack 3.6.7}}

The class contains the following monsters:{{refsrc|src/monst.c|145|version=NetHack 3.6.7}}

* {{monsymlink|acid blob}}
* {{monsymlink|quivering blob}}
* {{monsymlink|gelatinous cube}}

==Common traits==
Blobs are [[neutral]] [[amoeboid]]s that are [[unbreathing]] and lack several [[body parts]]: they have no limbs, eyes or heads. Each blob is generally slower-moving than an unhasted and unburdened [[hero]], and they have a tendency to wander around while moving. Blobs have [[sleep resistance]] and [[poison resistance]].

===Generation===
Randomly generated blobs are always created hostile except for the acid blob, which may generate as peaceful towards neutral characters.

==History==
The blob monster class first appears in [[NetHack 3.0.0]] - the acid blob, quivering blob and gelatinous cube all appear in previous versions of ''NetHack'', and NetHack 3.0.0 establishes the monster class and its current glyph to group them under.

